main event: Two civilians reported a sighting of circular, disc-shaped objects with a concave leading edge in Walla Walla, Washington on 21st April 1952, at 10:50 PM. The objects were gray in color, seen in daylight, and exhibited rapid, level maneuvers including standing still at an altitude of approximately 15,000 feet. No photograph or sketch of the objects is available.
interesting points: The sighting occurred at 10:50 PM and was reported by two civilians in Walla Walla, Washington.
The objects were circular, disc-shaped, and had a concave leading edge. They were gray in color and seen in daylight.

The source of the report is from two civilians employed by Walla Walla Canning Co.
